(4, 'Game of Power in Rajasthan', 'Ashish', 'Politics', '2020-07-21', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center; &quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-1944a8c8-7fff-f3a3-1cbb-322e02f2ef06&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;The political crisis started with friction between CM Ashok Gehlot and Deputy CM Sachin Pilot have taken dramatic turns in the past few days. After denial of the possibilities of joining BJP by Pilot and the call tapping incident done by Congress, the question remains the same: &ldquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; What is the future of political power in Rajasthan?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; &rdquo;. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-1944a8c8-7fff-f3a3-1cbb-322e02f2ef06&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-1944a8c8-7fff-f3a3-1cbb-322e0