(7, 'National Education Policy  2020', 'ASHISH & NAVNEET', 'Youth', '2020-07-31', '&lt;h1 style=&quot;text-align: center; &quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-f0924188-7fff-c88f-30f4-04cfc23d6faa&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 26pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-1555820d-7fff-6488-4cd1-a896f20d15c0&quot;&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h6 style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;The new National Education Policy 2020 approved by the Union Cabinet on Wednesday, major changes have been introduced to strengthen the basic structure of our current education system. These changes were much needed as the old education policy proved to be outdated and more exam - centric.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h6&gt;&lt;h6 style=&quot;text-align: left; &quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-f0924188-7fff-c88f-30f4-04cfc23d6faa&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 26pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-1555820d-7fff-6488-4cd1-a896f20d15c0&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-a11d6d23-7fff-46ae-7c82-e81736febec9&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h6&gt;&lt;h6 style=&quot;text-align: left; &quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-f0924188-7fff-c88f-30f4-04cfc23d6faa&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 26pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-1555820d-7fff-6488-4cd1-a896f20d15c0&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-a11d6d23-7fff-46ae-7c82-e81736febec9&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-3dd7d89a-7fff-7738-96de-f184a90ce0bf&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 17pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;Highlights of this Policy:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h6&gt;&lt;h6 style=&quot;text-align: left; &quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-f0924188-7fff-c88f-30f4-04cfc23d6faa&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 26pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-1555820d-7fff-6488-4cd1-a896f20d15c0&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-a11d6d23-7fff-46ae-7c82-e81736febec9&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-3dd7d89a-7fff-7738-96de-f184a90ce0bf&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 17pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;margin-left:36.0pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1&quot;&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;text-indent: -18pt; background-color: transparent; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN&quot; style=&quot;font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left: 36pt; text-indent: -18pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;text-indent: -18pt; background-color: transparent; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN&quot; style=&quot;font-size: 14pt; line-height: 115%;&quot;&gt;1) School Education&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN&quot; style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%&quot;&gt;New National Curriculum Framework for ECE, School, Teachers and Adult Education&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Board Examination will be Low Stakes, Based on Knowledge Application&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;The medium of Instruction till at least Grade 5, and preferably till Grade 8 and &lt;/span&gt;beyond in Home Language/ Mother tongue/ Regional Language&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;360-degree Holistic Progress Card of Child&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Tracking Student Progress for Achieving Learning Outcomes&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;National assessment centre - PARAKH&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;NTA to offer Common Entrance Exam for Admission TO HEIs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;National Professional Standards for Teachers (NPST)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Book Promotion Policy and Digital &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN&quot; style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%&quot;&gt;Libraries&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Transparent online self-disclosure for public oversight and accountability&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Universalization of Early Childhood Care Education (ECCE)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;National Mission on Foundational Literacy and Numeracy&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;5+3+3+4 Curricular and Pedagogical Structure&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Curriculum to integrate 21st Century Skills, Mathematical Thinking and &lt;/span&gt;Scientific temper&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;No &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Rigid Separation between Arts &amp;amp; Sciences, between Curricular and extra - &lt;/span&gt;curricular activities, between Vocational and Academic streams&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Education of Gifted Children&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Gender Inclusion Fund&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;KGBVs up to Grade 12&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Reduction in Curriculum to Core Concepts&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Vocational integration from Class 6 onwards&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;background-color: transparent; font-size: 12pt; text-indent: -18pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN&quot; style=&quot;font-size:17.0pt;\r\nline-height:115%&quot;&gt;       2)&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot; times=&quot;&quot; new=&quot;&quot; roman&quot;;&quot;=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;background-color: transparent; font-size: 12pt; text-indent: -18pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN&quot; style=&quot;font-size:17.0pt;line-height:115%&quot;&gt;Higher Education&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;50% Gross Enrolment Ratio by 2035&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Holistic and Multidisciplinary Education- Flexibility of Subjects&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Multiple Entry/Exit&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;UG &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Programme - 3 or 4 years&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;PG Programme - 1 or 2 years&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Integrated 5 year bachelor\'s/Master\'s&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;M Phil to be discontinued&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Credit Transfer and Academic Bank of Credits&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;HEIs: Research Intensive/ Teaching Intensive Universities and Autonomous Degree-Granting&lt;/span&gt; College&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Model Multidisciplinary Education and Research University (MERU)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h6&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-1555820d-7fff-6488-4cd1-a896f20d15c0&quot;&gt;&lt;h6 style=&quot;text-align: left; line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-9dd2c3c7-7fff-209c-fdc1-273bb534ccdc&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;The National Education Policy (NEP) drew favourable reactions among academicians and organisations. Many called the policy a welcome move towards overhauling the education system in the country while CMP terms it unilateral drive to destroy education.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Let us see the points presented in opposition to some of the reform:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: center; &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h6&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;table class=&quot;table table-bordered&quot;&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center; &quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-f0bbb547-7fff-a474-5c19-34b2853f842b&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Reform in NEP&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center; &quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-847d9cbe-7fff-fb4b-6273-502dc7fef504&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;What people said in opposition&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-a7175184-7fff-2895-035b-2aa4bd4710ad&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Vocational education will start in schools from the 6th grade and will include internships.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-fb0c2825-7fff-5366-8f32-c441d5361cb5&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;The policy document wants school and college education to ultimately have 50% of students going into vocational education. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Vocational education in India isn&rsquo;t as creative and meaningful as in other countries. Here, the vocational courses are designed by the industry and not by educationists.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;list-style-type: disc; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Anita Rampal (Professor and former Dean, Faculty of education, Delhi University)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-0c2b41c4-7fff-a643-66a2-b500a81cbe6a&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;The Centre and the States will work together to increase the public investment in Education sector to reach 6% of GDP at the earliest.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-bfd39164-7fff-ebf9-8d3a-d8a6b81b2647&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;The goal of 6% of GDP to be spent on education was first articulated in 1948! Every Govt articulates this target&amp;amp; then comes up against its own Finance Ministry. In the last 6 years, ModiGovt expenditure in education has declined in real terms. How will it reach 6%?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-e23c5a19-7fff-24e8-9e7b-4001fe2af7fe&quot;&gt;&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;list-style-type: disc; font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Shahi Tharoor (former HRD minister)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-ed63b2ce-7fff-834a-dc8f-8b77cd1f9087&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;UG education can be of 3 or 4 years with multiple exit options and appropriate certification within this period. For example, Certificate after 1 year, Advanced Diploma after 2 years, Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree after 3 years and Bachelor&rsquo;s with Research after 4 years.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-4e0aa6ac-7fff-5772-a00b-4f7b43be204f&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;They said you can &quot;exit&quot; whenever you &quot;want&quot; from your graduation, do people leave study out of will? Or is it the poverty, casteism and gender discrimination that forced them to leave. Without challenging this how can we ensure education as a right for all?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;        - Dipsita (All India Joint Secretary,       &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Students\' Federation of India -SFI) through Twitter.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-3fbcf10a-7fff-7545-3e56-bc341993287c&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;5+3+3+4 Curricular and Pedagogical Structure&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-f5f92fa7-7fff-ae41-cd11-49f267a54330&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;The policy has segregated classes I and II with Anganwadi education. This carries the danger of minimalising the two school years, with some institution possibly considering them merely as play years.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;list-style-type: disc; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Anita Rampal (Professor and former Dean, Faculty of education, Delhi University)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-0d1fec79-7fff-f13a-ba81-1dc37bc8ff5d&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;NEP 2020 aims to increase the Gross Enrolment Ratio in higher education including vocational education from 26.3% (2018) to 50% by 2035. 3.5 Crore new seats will be added to Higher education institutions.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-f6567836-7fff-44e0-e4c5-6a7bfb59fef0&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;The goals of 50% Gross Enrolment Ratio in higher education and 100% in secondary school are laudable, but when you realise it&rsquo;s currently 25.8% in Higher Edn &amp;amp; 68% in Class 9, you wonder if such targets are any more realistic than the Govt&rsquo;s solar-energy commitments at Paris.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;list-style-type: disc; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Shahi Tharoor (former HRD minister)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-dcf46d5c-7fff-7d7b-dc15-f9432a7535f7&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Affiliation of colleges is to be phased out in 15 years and a stage-wise mechanism is to be established for granting graded autonomy to colleges. Over a period of time, it is envisaged that every college would develop into either an Autonomous degree-granting College or a constituent college of a university.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-a47b5e56-7fff-c995-4bf6-54a7bb347804&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Financial autonomy means Educational Institutions finding their own finance with increasing fees and cutting cost such as scholarships. The door education now only opens for those with money.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;list-style-type: disc; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;PA Mohamed Riyas (All India President, DYFI) through Twitter&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;h1 style=&quot;text-align: center; &quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-1555820d-7fff-6488-4cd1-a896f20d15c0&quot;&gt;&lt;h6 style=&quot;text-align: left; line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-9dd2c3c7-7fff-209c-fdc1-273bb534ccdc&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: center; &quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h6&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h5 style=&quot;color: rgb(128, 128, 128); text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-a653cfec-7fff-53d4-587f-31f476064b3d&quot;&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;h5 style=&quot;color: rgb(128, 128, 128); text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-a653cfec-7fff-53d4-587f-31f476064b3d&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;h5 style=&quot;color: rgb(128, 128, 128); text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-a653cfec-7fff-53d4-587f-31f476064b3d&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;', '03:52:02 PM', 'National-Education-Policy-2020', '&lt;div data-height=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.kialo.com/indias-new-national-education-policy-is-beneficial-for-youth-39242&quot;&gt;India\'s new National Education Policy is beneficial for youth?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &mdash; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.kialo.com/&quot;&gt;kialo.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;script async src=\'https://www.kialo.com/assets/frontend-buildtag-stable-671/static/js/embedded-kialo.min.js\' charset=\'utf-8\'&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&lt;/div&gt;', 'https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/delhi/experts-differ-over-focus-on-vocational-edu-in-schools/articleshow/77250784.cms\r\n\r\nhttps://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/much-to-welcome-in-national-education-policy-but-shashi-tharoor-highlights-some-challenges/story-W86DVZPz0adXwrcs0SaUMO.html\r\n\r\nhttps://twitter.com/riyasdyfi/status/1288757531972472833?s=20\r\n\r\nhttps://twitter.com/DharDipsita/status/1288755112207212547?s=20', 'national edu policy aa', 'The National Education Policy (NEP) drew favourable reactions among academicians and organisations. Many called the policy a welcome move towards overhauling the education system in the country while CMP terms it unilateral drive to destroy education.  Let us see the points presented in opposition to some of the reform:', 'NEP, Youth, National, Education, Policy, 2020, India', 'Post'),
(8, 'Race to The Red Planet', 'Navneet & Ashish', 'General', '2020-08-01', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;text-align: center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:26pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-b1144e26-7fff-16ad-4946-f0ddb6517662&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;text-align: center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;NASA launches its Mars Perseverance Rover on July 30th at 17:20 IST from Cape Canaveral Airforce Station, Florida. This was the third mission in a row to blast off for Mars in the last two weeks, after UAE and China. So is there a Martian Space race between the tech giants. Let\'s know more about this below.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:16pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;US - Launch of Perseverance &amp; Ingenuity&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;NASA had successfully launched its Mars Perseverance Rover &amp; Ingenuity Helicopter on July 30. The main aim of the Mars Perseverance Rover is to seek signs of ancient life and collect rock and soil samples for a possible return to Earth. The duration of the mission is expected to be at least one Mars year which is equivalent to 687 days on Earth. The Mars Perseverance Rover is expected to land on Mars on February 18, 2021, after covering a distance of 300 million miles (482.8 million km approximately). The landing site of the rover will be the Jezero Crater on the Red Planet. This is the third launch to Mars after China&rsquo;s rover-orbiter combo and a United Arab Emirates orbiter launched last week.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial; font-size: 16pt; font-weight: 700; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:16pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;UAE - The HOPE Probe or the Al Amal&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;The United Arab Emirates also launched its first mission to Mars on 19th July as it strives to develop its scientific and technological capabilities. The Hope Probe blasted off from Japan\'s Tanegashima Space Center for a seven - month journey to the red planet , where it will orbit and send back data from the atmosphere. The Emirates Mars Mission has cost $200 million according to the Minister for Advanced Sciences Sarah Amiri. It aims to provide a complete picture of the Martian Atmosphere for the first time, studying daily and seasonal changes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:17pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Chinese Tianwen-1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;China has successfully launched its first major interplanetary mission to Mars. The launch begins a long seven-month journey through deep space, and once the mission reaches the Red Planet, Called Tianwen-1, China&rsquo;s mission consists of a Martian orbiter, lander, and rover. The trio launched on top of the Long March 5 from China&rsquo;s Wenchang Spacecraft Launch Site in the early morning hours of July 23rd. The Long March 5 is one of China&rsquo;s most powerful rockets, and this mission marked just the fourth launch ever for this type of vehicle.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:18pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Why is everyone going to Mars at the same time?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Earth takes 365 days to orbit the Sun and Mars takes a slower 687 days. That&rsquo;s 1.88 Earth years, which puts Mars and Earth reasonably close to an orbital resonance of 2:1. So just over every two years Earth catches-up on Mars and the planets briefly line-up. At that point, they&rsquo;re closest together. So just before that point, the journey between the two planets takes the least amount of time.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;The launch window differs depending on your launch vehicle, which typically gives you maybe a day or two on either end of that launch window. The launch window is reasonably long, certainly enough to cope with short periods of bad weather.&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;However, if for any reason it doesn&rsquo;t happen, the whole thing will need to be postponed until the next biannual launch window opens in 2022.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;That&rsquo;s the next &ldquo;year of Mars.&rdquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial; font-size: 18pt; font-weight: 700; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Future of Space: Competition or Collaboration?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Whether there will be a collaboration between countries to explore space is a complicated matter, given the current political climate. Today, competition between countries is expanding and there are constant economic confrontations, which will likely limit cooperation for the near future. Additionally, the sharing of technology between nations seems to be declining rather than expanding, which is essential for space collaboration to result in progress. Continuing technology advances will likely see more individual nations and companies competing in space. Moreover, with the USA talking about a Space Force and Ant-Satellite systems being used in space by China, one must consider the implications of the militarization of space. A drive for overall dominance and control, indicative of the original landing.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;font-weight:normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-1d47ed75-7fff-4712-2bca-e571a027f1a6&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h5 style=&quot;color: rgb(128, 128, 128); text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Arial&quot; color=&quot;#424242&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.6667px; white-space: pre-wrap; font-family: Tahoma;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;', '04:20:49 PM', 'Race-to-The-Red-Planet', '', '', 'race to mars', 'NASA launches its Mars Perseverance Rover on July 30th at 17:20 IST from Cape Canaveral Airforce Station, Florida. This was the third mission in a row to blast off for Mars in the last two weeks, after UAE and China. So is there a Martian Space race between the tech giants. Let\'s know more about this below.\r\n', 'Mars, Race, Red planet, 2020', 'Post'),
(13, 'India & China must continue the talks for ensuring full restoration of Peace', 'Sumit', 'General', '2020-09-05', '&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h5&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#000000&quot;&gt;Rajnath Singh&lt;/font&gt;:&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Indian Defence minister Rajnath Singh said that India\'s position on the entire details including the Line of actual Control (LAC) as well as the Galvan Valley in the western sector of the India-China border area in the last few months is clear.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 0.9rem;&quot;&gt;Singh said in the statement that it was emphasized that the actions of Chinese troops, including a large number of soldiers, their Rajnath aggressive behavior and attempts to unilaterally change the status quo were in violation of bilateral agreements.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Singh said that both sides should seek guidance from the consensus of the leaders that the maintenance of peace and tranquility in the India-China border areas was essential for the further development of our bilateral relations.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h5&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#000000&quot;&gt;Wei Fenghe&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Chinese Defence minister Wei Fenghe said that both sides should clearly implement the agreement reached between Prime Minister Modi and President Xi Jinping and continue to resolve issues through dialogue and consultation.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Fenghe said strictly follow the various bilateral agreements, strengthen the regulation of frontline troops and not undertake any provocative actions that might escalate the situation.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Fenghe said that two sides should focus on the overall situation of India-China relations and work together to de-escalate the situation as soon as possible, and maintain peace and tranquillity in the India-China border areas.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', '08:12:23 PM', 'India-China-must-continue-the-talks-for-ensuring-full-restoration-of-Peace', '', '', 'India and China must continue the talks for ensuring full restoration of Peace', '', 'India, China, Peace, LAC, Army, Talks, Pangong', 'Report');
