(10, 'NEET and JEE exams during Covid-19 Situation?', 'Ashish & facts collected by Mohit', 'Youth', '2020-08-24', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:3pt;&quot; id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-2ccd1c47-7fff-584a-7ab2-e353fdef0443&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 26pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h5 style=&quot;line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 3pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;What has happened?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-faccbbd4-7fff-f5cc-5a6d-9f770cb1c9e3&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&ldquo;Career of students cannot be put in peril. We find no merit in the petition. The petition is dismissed&rdquo;, the bench which comprised justices Arun Mishra, BR Gavai and Krishna Murari said.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;The SC hearing on JEE Main and NEET had two pleas of different views regarding the postponement. One petition was demanding the further postponement of JEE Main and NEET.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Another petition praying that NEET and JEE should be held as per schedule was withdrawn by the petitioner after the court rejected the plea seeking a postponement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;table class=&quot;table table-bordered&quot;&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center; &quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#000000&quot;&gt;What Petition said&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center; &quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#000000&quot;&gt;What Supreme court said&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot; id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-4543d69b-7fff-49ee-a2fc-4b18a982e579&quot;&gt;The best recourse at this stage can be to wait for some more time, let Covid-19 Crisis subside and then only conduct these Exams, in order to save the lives of the students and their parents.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot; id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-5ac93f6f-7fff-a953-9d96-ec12644c9b96&quot;&gt;A three-judge bench headed by Justice Arun Mishra said that &ldquo;life has to go on&rdquo; despite COVID and the court cannot put the career of students in peril by interfering with the decision of the National Testing Agency.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px;&quot; id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-1da47214-7fff-0159-347e-d3672842cd77&quot;&gt;&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Conducting JEE and NEET at this stage will put lives of lakhs of young students in danger, the petition filed by 11 JEE/NEET aspirants said&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px;&quot; id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-71253f31-7fff-29d3-bae1-80fe73f2f962&quot;&gt;&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&ldquo;You (lawyers) have demanded the opening of physical courts. But you want exams to be postponed. Postponement of exams is a loss for the country,&rdquo; the bench said.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px;&quot; id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-4f3df0b9-7fff-bdd6-f58e-d4974d08d922&quot;&gt;&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Petitioner&rsquo;s lawyer Alakh Alok Srivastava said that vaccine for COVID is &ldquo;on its way&rdquo; and he is not seeking an indefinite postponement of the exams.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px;&quot; id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-4f9c2805-7fff-fc40-b0fd-aef83732f2aa&quot;&gt;&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;The apex court found no merit in this point due to uncertainty of launch of the vaccine in India.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;&quot; id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-4fe5fea2-7fff-7465-c0bb-7c18d488abc0&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Reactions in support of not postponing the exam:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;The Medical Council of India (MCI) has submitted before the Supreme Court that the postponement of the National Eligibility Cum Entrance Test (NEET) Undergraduate (UG) 2020 shall be a &quot;drastic deviation&quot; from the academic schedule which &quot;may affect the subsequent academic years&quot; of the students.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px;&quot; id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-09a9e1db-7fff-cd62-2e3b-1fa63ef9a2f8&quot;&gt;&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Gujarat Parents Association has requested the Supreme Court to let the examination be conducted on the scheduled date. The petition cites that the delay would severely affect the academic calendar and the continuous change in dates causes mental stress to students.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.92;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:15pt;&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&ldquo;Medical admissions are time-bound, and therefore, it makes no sense to further delay NEET, which will eventually delay the admissions process as well. Leaving an entire batch of medical seats vacant will be unfair because next year, the intake capacity of medical institutes will remain the same but the applicants will double in number, which will lead to more chaos,&rdquo; said activist Sudha Shenoy, who is the parent of an aspirant.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.92;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:15pt;&quot; id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-43e5ff70-7fff-8310-f90b-dfe21310f6e0&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Reaction in support of postponing the exam:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.92;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:15pt;&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&ldquo;The central government is playing with the lives of millions of students in the name JEE-NEET Exams. My request to the Center is to cancel both these exams immediately and make an alternative arrangement for admission this year. In this time of unprecedented crisis, an unprecedented step will lead to a solution. Today in 21st century India, we cannot think of an alternate option for entrance examinations! This is not possible. Only the intention of the government should be to think in the interest of students, instead of conducting NEET-JEE, there can be thousands of safe ways,&quot; said Deputy Chief Minister of Delhi and Education Minister Manish Sisodia.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px;&quot; id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-705d2b53-7fff-fc29-3314-b1bfec7c66ac&quot;&gt;&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.92;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:15pt;&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;BJP MP Subramanian Swamy writes to PM Modi, calls for postponement of competitive exams:&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.92;margin-left: 36pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:15pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&quot;I write this urgent letter because of my authentic information from every part of India that required infrastructure of the country is not yet in place for students to take the NEET/JEE &amp; other Competitive Exams. In the city of Bombay for example, there is no public transport and people have to come from in the adjacent areas, often 20kms to 30kms away. There is widespread desperation amongst the youth since this exam is make or break for them and they have to take it fully prepared. Moreover, the Supreme Court judgment doesn\'t bind the government at all, on whether to now or two weeks later or two months later, the examinations. It is a policy decision of the Government. Therefore, I request you to please inform the Ministry of Education that these exams can be conducted after the Deepavali. I have spoken to Minister Ramesh Pokhriyal and he was sympathetic to my suggestion but naturally, since this would require your concurrence, hence I am writing this urgent letter to you.&quot;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.92;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:15pt;&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;#Satyagrah_AgainstExamInCovid started on Twitter by students and some students are going for a hunger strike.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h6 segoe=&quot;&quot; ui&quot;,=&quot;&quot; roboto,=&quot;&quot; &quot;helvetica=&quot;&quot; neue&quot;,=&quot;&quot; arial,=&quot;&quot; sans-serif,=&quot;&quot; &quot;apple=&quot;&quot; color=&quot;&quot; emoji&quot;,=&quot;&quot; &quot;segoe=&quot;&quot; ui=&quot;&quot; symbol&quot;,=&quot;&quot; &quot;noto=&quot;&quot; emoji&quot;;=&quot;&quot; color:=&quot;&quot; rgb(128,=&quot;&quot; 128,=&quot;&quot; 128);=&quot;&quot; text-align:=&quot;&quot; center;&quot;=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;text-align: center; &quot;&gt;&lt;hr id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-fd95d481-7fff-fdec-dccd-7f1a258b4808&quot;&gt;&lt;/h6&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', '03:48:59 PM', 'NEET-and-JEE-exams-during-Covid-19-Situation-', '', 'https://www.ndtv.com/education/postponing-neet-will-be-drastic-deviation-from-academic-schedule-mci-supreme-court/amp\r\n\r\nhttps://www.google.com/amp/s/m.hindustantimes.com/india-news/jee-neet-postponement-all-you-need-to-know/story-eyMlyXSS7IeRji5icIoT0H_amp.html\r\n\r\nhttps://www.ndtv.com/education/jee-main-neet-2020-cancel-exams-and-make-alternative-arrangement-says-manish-sisodia/amp\r\n', 'NEET and JEE', '\"Career of students cannot be put in peril. We find no merit in the petition. The petition is dismissedâ€, the bench which comprised justices Arun Mishra, BR Gavai and Krishna Murari said.', 'JEE Mains, NEET, Exams, Covid-19, Supreme Court', 'Post'),
(11, 'COVID Vaccine in India: A Hope, True or False', 'Ashish', 'Covid19', '2020-09-04', '&lt;h1 align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#000000&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot; times=&quot;&quot; new=&quot;&quot; roman&quot;;&quot;=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 0.9rem;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;Since the outbreak of Covid-19 in the world, several countries are working intensely to develop a vaccine to fight the pandemic. The recent development in this field was Russian adenovirus vector-based vaccine registered by the Russian Ministry of Health on August 11 which became the first registered COVID-19 vaccine on the market.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;Currently, there are about 165 different vaccines for COVID-19 being developed around the world. About 30 different Indian companies are trying to produce a vaccine to fight the infection, out of which WHO has given approvals to seven vaccine candidates, which are in different stages of testing and clinical studies now.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;These development have given hope to India which is currently at number 3 in the world&rsquo;s ranking in COVID cases. Let us try to see what experts have said on the availability of the vaccine in India.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h4&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;â— &lt;/span&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#000000&quot;&gt;The positive hope:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#000000&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;1. In India, phase-2 trials of the Oxford-AstraZeneca vaccine began last week, and about 1.600 participants are likely to be enrolled for the combined phase-2 and phase-3 trials. This vaccine is undergoing phase-3 testing in several countries, including the US, Brazil, England and South Africa.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;2. Two homegrown vaccine candidates &mdash; Covaxin by Bharat Biotech and ZyCoV-D by Zydus Cadila have already started the phase II clinical trial.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;3. &quot;We are not lagging behind anyone else in the whole world in our efforts to contribute towards the vaccine against COVID... In India, we have about 7-8 vaccine candidates, three of them in the clinical trial phases and rest in the pre-clinical trials and by the end of this year, we hope to be able to get a vaccine against COVID,&quot; Union health and family welfare minister Dr Harsh Vardhan said.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;4. &quot;There had been \'no side effects\' in the phase I trial of Covaxin,&quot; Dr E Venkata Rao, principal&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;investigator of the trial at Institute of Medical Sciences and SUM Hospital, faculty of medical sciences, said.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h4&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;â— &lt;/span&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#000000&quot;&gt;India should avoid false hope on coronavirus vaccine - Health experts&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#000000&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;The Joint Task Force of eminent public health experts on 31st August 2020, wrote to Prime&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;Minister Narendra Modi and said it must be assumed that an effective vaccine against the novel coronavirus &quot;would not be available in the near future&quot;. They also said that any false sense of hope that this panacea is just around the corner must be avoided.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;In a joint statement, experts of the Indian Public Health Association (IPHA), Indian Association&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of Preventive and Social Medicine (IAPSM), and Indian Association of Epidemiologists (IAE) said, &quot;Vaccines do not have any role in current ongoing coronavirus pandemic control in India.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;The group\'s third joint statement on hope for a coronavirus vaccine against Covid-19 states,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&quot;Vaccines with proven efficacy and safety, as and when available, should be administered according to the WHO\'s \'strategic allocation\' approach or a multi-tiered risk-based approach.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;The experts have suggested the following measures and plan of action to the government:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;1. No lockdown, only short defined &quot;cluster&quot; restrictions duration to be imposed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;2. It\'s time now to move towards normalcy. The opening of schools and other educational institutions&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;could be started in a graded manner.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;3. Quarantine and Isolation Policy should be community-friendly.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;4. Pragmatic testing as a control strategy. Universal scaling up of testing at the current&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;community transmission stage of the pandemic may not be an optimal control strategy and will divert attention and resources from control measures.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;5. Periodic sero-surveillance survey for monitoring the pandemic.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;6. Increase healthcare expenditure to 5 per cent of GDP.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;7. Public health cadre at national and state levels.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;Also, researchers worry that, even with India&rsquo;s experience as a vaccine manufacturer, its companies will struggle to produce enough doses sufficiently fast to bring its own huge outbreak under control. On top of that, it will be an immense logistical challenge to distribute the doses to people in rural and remote regions.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-d41518b6-7fff-1669-b8ae-01b807692f22&quot;&gt;&lt;h6 segoe=&quot;&quot; ui&quot;,=&quot;&quot; roboto,=&quot;&quot; &quot;helvetica=&quot;&quot; neue&quot;,=&quot;&quot; arial,=&quot;&quot; sans-serif,=&quot;&quot; &quot;apple=&quot;&quot; color=&quot;&quot; emoji&quot;,=&quot;&quot; &quot;segoe=&quot;&quot; ui=&quot;&quot; symbol&quot;,=&quot;&quot; &quot;noto=&quot;&quot; emoji&quot;;=&quot;&quot; color:=&quot;&quot; rgb(128,=&quot;&quot; 128,=&quot;&quot; 128);=&quot;&quot; text-align:=&quot;&quot; center;&quot;=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;text-align: center; &quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/h6&gt;', '03:42:27 PM', 'COVID-Vaccine-in-India-A-Hope-True-or-False', '', 'https://www.indiatoday.in/amp/india/story/avoid-false-hope-on-coronavirus-vaccine-discontinue-lockdown-health-experts-write-to-pm-modi-1717267-2020-09-01\r\n\r\nhttps://www.livemint.com/news/india/covid-19-vaccine-in-india-may-be-ready-by-the-year-end-says-health-minister-11598864928873.html\r\n\r\nhttps://www.nature.com/articles/d41586-020-02507-x\r\n\r\nhttps://indianexpress.com/article/explained/september-2-coronavirus-vaccine-latest-covid-19-updates-6579651/\r\n', 'COVID vaccine hope', 'The recent developments in the field of vaccine for Corona virus have given hope to India which is currently at number 3 in the worldâ€™s ranking in COVID-19 cases. Let us try to see what experts have said on the availability of the vaccine in India.', 'Corona ,Covid ,Coronavirus ,Stayhome ,Quarantine , Virus , Lockdown ', 'Post'),
(12, 'Centre\'s Bill on Official Languages in J&K Facing Opposition?', 'Sumit', 'General', '2020-09-04', '&lt;h5&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#000000&quot; style=&quot;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Government&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;â— The Central Government\'s move that the adoption of Hindi, Kashmiri, Dogri, Urdu and English has taken many people by surprise.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;â— It has also triggered demands for the inclusion of more languages in the proposed legislation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;â— An official, wishing anonymity, said that parliament will exercise powers conferred upon the J&amp;amp;K assembly to adopt these languages as official languages of the UT.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h5&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#000000&quot; style=&quot;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Opposition&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;â— Choudhary Zulfikar said Gojri and Pahari languages should be included in the proposed legislation of official languages as these are spoken across J&amp;amp;K.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;â— Under the sixth schedule of the constitution of the erstwhile state of J&amp;amp;K, Kashmiri, Dogri, Balti (Pali), Dardi, Punjabi, Pahari, Ladakhi and Gojri were regional languages of the state.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14.4px;&quot;&gt;â— Lateef-ul-Zaman Deva said, Enforcing more than two languages in J&amp;amp;K will lead to linguistic polarisation with genuine demands for the inclusion of Gojri, Pahari and Punjabi.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', '03:16:30 PM', 'Centre-s-Bill-on-Official-Languages-in-J-K-Facing-Opposition-', '', '', 'Centre Bill on Official Languages in J and K Facing Opposition', '', 'Jammu & Kashmir, Language, Opposition, Hindi, Kashmiri, Dogri, Urdu, English\r\n', 'Report');

